Official Documentation : https://developers.chatwoot.com/self-hosted/deployment/docker
Version : v4.5.2

Steps to deploy Chatwoot using docker-compose
â€‹
1. Install Docker on your VM

apt-get update
apt-get upgrade
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com -o get-docker.sh
sudo sh get-docker.sh
apt install docker-compose-plugin
â€‹
2. Download the required files

# Download the env file template
wget -O .env https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chatwoot/chatwoot/develop/.env.example
# Download the Docker compose template
wget -O docker-compose.yaml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chatwoot/chatwoot/develop/docker-compose.production.yaml
â€‹
3. Configure environment variables
Tweak the .env and docker-compose.yaml according to your preferences. Refer to the available environment variables. You could also remove the dependant services like Postgres, Redis etc., in favor of managed services configured via environment variables.

nano .env
# update docker-compose.yaml same postgres pass
nano docker-compose.yaml
â€‹
4. Prepare the database

docker compose run --rm rails bundle exec rails db:chatwoot_prepare
â€‹
5. Start the services

docker compose up -d

Chatwoot
It is an open-source customer engagement platform, often called an alternative to Intercom or Zendesk.
It provides live chat + multichannel inbox + automation for customer support and sales.

ðŸ”¹ Chatwoot Usage
1. Live Chat on Website

Embed a chat widget on your website.
Customers can reach support instantly.
Supports real-time chat, typing indicators, file sharing, rich messages.

2. Omnichannel Inbox

Centralized shared inbox for different platforms:

Website live chat
WhatsApp Business
Facebook Messenger
Instagram DMs
Twitter/X DMs
Telegram
Line
Email (IMAP/SMTP)
SMS (via Twilio, Vonage)
